main event: Multiple UFO sightings were reported in San Diego, California, primarily involving ground-visual observations of lights and objects in the sky during February 1955.
interesting points: One report described a large blinking red light stationary at times and moving rapidly 33 miles,Observations suggested the presence of a possible meteor shower with multiple silver streaks in formations,Several individual reports indicated ground-visual sightings of unidentified glowing objects,One witness claimed to have seen an object changing from red to white with no wings,Reports included both civilian and military sources, with varying lengths of observation.
sighted object: blinking red light and glowing objects
witness description: Multiple witnesses including civilians and military personnel
